ng%20harmful%20substances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20dad%20knew%20I%20wanted%20to%20give%20up%20drugs%20and%20drinking%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20close%20with%20my%20dad%20and%20was%20honest%20about%20my%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsobriety-benefits-sober-alcohol-drinking-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20problem%20with%20booze%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20regular%20phone%20conversations%20with%20him%2C%20even%20though%20he%20admitted%20to%20me%20that%20every%20time%20I%20phoned%20him%2C%20he%20worried%20about%20what%20I%20would%20tell%20him.%20He%20joked%20sometimes%20that%20when%20he%20saw%20my%20name%20flash%20up%20on%20his%20screen%2C%20it%20would%20give%20him%20a%20mild%20panic%20attack.%20In%20fact%2C%20my%20whole%20family%20worried%2C%20but%20they%20also%20told%20me%20they%20knew%20there%20was%20no%20reasoning%20with%20me%20%E2%80%94%20I%20was%20so%20stubborn%20with%20everything%20else%2C%20they%20felt%20there%20was%20no%20point%20in%20trying%20to%20get%20me%20to%20stop%20drinking%20or%20taking%20drugs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20days%20after%20I%20was%20discharged%20from%20the%20emergency%20ward%2C%20it%20was%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrandmother-family-caregiver-death-guilt-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20my%20Nan's%20funeral%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20had%20died%20earlier%20in%20the%20year%20after%20a%20COVID%20outbreak%20at%20the%20care%20home%20she%20lived%20in.%20Her%20favorite%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BLife's%20a%20bitch%2C%20and%20then%20you%20die%2C%26quot%3B%20stuck%20with%20me%20that%20whole%20year%20as%20I%20tore%20through%20my%20own%20struggle%20with%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20dad%20was%20now%20without%20both%20of%20his%20parents%20and%20was%20dealing%20with%20his%20unwavering%20grief%2C%20an%20intoxicated%20daughter%2C%20and%20the%20task%20of%20selling%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-mom-divorced-multigenerational-hom