d4e76e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221560%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBryan%20Boyle%20onboard%20a%20container%20ship%20in%20Alaska.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Bryan%20Boyle%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBryan%20Boyle%2C%20a%20YouTuber%20and%20second%20mate%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcargo-ship-living-quarters-pictures-tour-youtube-video-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecargo%20ship%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20detailed%20how%20workers%20are%20trained%20to%20deal%20with%20emergencies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20merchant%20mariner%20said%20incidents%20like%20the%20Baltimore%20bridge%20collapse%20are%20incredibly%20rare%20at%20sea.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBoyle%20said%20he%20was%20on%20a%20ship%20that%20lost%20power%20briefly%20and%20his%20training%20kicked%20in.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20second%20mate%20Bryan%20Boyle%2C%20a%20merchant%20mariner%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2F%40BryanBoyle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EYouTuber%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20who%20has%20worked%20as%20a%20deck%20officer%20on%20various%20cargo%20ships%20for%20over%20a%20decade.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20a%20deck%20officer%20for%20almost%2012%20years.%20I'm%20responsible%20for%20watching%20out%20for%20the%20safety%20of%20the%20crew%2C%20cargo%2C%20and%20the%20ship%20itself%20by%20helping%20navigate%20and%20maneuver%20the%20ship%2C%20as%20well%20as%20facilitating%20communications%20and%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmergency%20situations%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaltimore-bridge-collapse-insurance-losses-francis-scott-key-lloyds-london-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFrancis%20Scott%20Key%20Bridge%20collapse%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20rare%20at%20sea.%20I've%20never%20faced%20any%20major%20emergencies%20while%20working%20aboard%20a%20cargo%20ship%2C%20aside%20from%20a%20minor%20fire%20and%20an%20instance%20where%20my%20ship%20temporarily%20lost%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20in%202019%2C%20I%20was%20on%20a%20cargo%20ship%20in%20the%20North%20Sea.%20I%20was%20a%20second%20mate%20and%20assigned%20to%20keep%20watch%20from%20midnight%20to%204%20a.m.%20Around%202%20a.m.%2C%20the%20whole%20ship%20went%20dark.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20temporarily%20lost%20all%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20get%20pretty%20chaotic%20when%20the%20ship%20goes%20dark%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20if%20it's%20already%20dark%20outside.%20Without%20the%20lights%2C%20it's%20completely%20pitch%20black%20on%20the%20bridge%2C%20a%20platform%20on%20the%20ship%20where%20you%20can%20navigate%20the%20vessel.%20The%20darkness%20was%20followed%20by%20the%20chaos%20of%20all%20of%20the%20electronics%20booting%20back%20up%20and%20the%20engine%20alarm%20sounding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20only%20took%20a%20few%20moments%20for%20the%20backup%20emergency%20diesel%20generator%20to%20turn%20on.%20It's%20programmed%20to%20automatically%20turn%20on.%20It%20controls%20all%20the%20navigation%20equipment%20and%20the%20emergency%20lighting.%20It%20also%20powers%20the%20steering.%20But%2C%20the%20main%20engine%20won't%20run%20off%20the%20emergency%20generator.%20We%20also%20have%20multiple%20battery%20backup%20stations%20on%20the%20ship%20that%20will%20keep%20some%20equipment%2C%20like%20the%20navigation%20equipment%2C%20powered%20on%20but%20with%20limited%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20can%20be%20a%20lot%20to%20deal%20with%20at%20once%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we're%20operating%20these%20vessels%20outside%20of%20water%20areas%20that%20require%20a%20pilot%2C%20like%20a%20port%20or%20bridge%2C%20it's%20usually%20just%20the%20officer%20and%20the%20helmsman%20or%20lookout%20who%20are%20keeping%20watch%20on%20the%20bridge.%20So%20it%20was%20just%20the%20two%20of%20us%20up%20there%20when%20the%20power%20went%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20very%20first%20things%20you%20do%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20the%20power%20goes%20out%20%E2%80%94%20before%20you%20even%20call%20the%20captain%20%E2%80%94%20you're%20making%20sure%3A%20Do%20I%20still%20have%20steering%20here%3F%20Do%20I%20need%20to%20switch%20over%20the%20steering%20to%20emergency%20steering%3F%20Switching%20the%20steering%20isn't%20as%20simple%20as%20flipping%20a%20switch%20and%20it%20requires%20coordinating%20with%20another%20worker%20in%20the%20steering%20room%20who%20can%20take%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20lose%20power%2C%20your%20immediate%20main%20focus%20is%20to%20avoid%20hitting%20anybody%20else%20or%20running%20aground.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20thing%20you%20do%20is%20notify%20the%20captain.%20If%20you%20have%20no%20power%2C%20your%20phone%20lines%20aren't%20going%20to%20work%20so%20we're%20trained%20to%20tap%20the%20general%20alarm%20a%20couple%20of%20times.%20The%20general%20alarm%20is%20on%20a%20battery%20backup%20system%2C%20so%20that's%20exactly%20what%20I%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22youtube%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F3T-wFfPm37U%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22How%20We%20Steer%20A%20Cargo%20Ship%20%7C%20Life%20At%20Sea%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20the%20captain%20came%20up%20to%20the%20bridge%20and%20I%20briefed%20him%20on%20what%20was%20going%20on.%20The%20first%20thing%20he%20wanted%20to%20know%20was%20if%20there%20was%20any%20traffic%20or%20anything%20around%20us.%20In%20that%20case%2C%20fortunately%2C%20the%20closest%20vessel%20to%20us%20was%20about%20a%20mile%20away%2C%20which%20seems%20like%20a%20lot%20but%20it's%20actually%20not%20%E2%80%94%20a%20lot%20of%20times%20that's%20the%20minimum%20distance%20you'd%20want%20for%20a%20point%20of%20approach%20from%20another%20vessel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ships%20can%20be%20sluggish%20to%20maneuver%2C%20especially%20when%20you've%20lost%20your%20power.%20You're%20going%20to%20start%20losing%20speed%20so%20your%20rotors%20become%20less%20and%20less%20effective.%20Or%2C%20God%20forbid%2C%20you%20actually%20lose%20full%20control%20of%20your%20steering%2C%20now%20you're%20at%20the%20whim%20of%20wherever%20it%20went%20down.%20That%20could%20be%20disastrous%20if%20it%20were%20turning%20because%20the%20ship%20would%20hold%20that%20turn%20and%20build%20up%20more%20and%20more%20momentum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuckily%2C%20in%20my%20situation%2C%20I%20still%20had%20steering%20power.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20the%20helmsman%20confirmed%20we%20had%20proper%20steering.%20And%20I%20was%20looking%20at%20my%20radars.%20I%20was%20also%20already%20visually%20aware%20of%20my%20surroundings%20and%20where%20we%20were%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20depth%20of%20the%20water.%20So%20we%20just%20kind%20of%20carried%20out%20the%20watch%20as%20normal.%20We%20were%20in%20communication%20with%20the%20engine%20room%2C%20trying%20to%20get%20an%20update%20on%20when%20to%20expect%20to%20have%20the%20power%20back%20on.%20We%20also%20communicated%20with%20the%20nearby%20ship.%20I%20radioed%20into%20that%20other%20vessel%20just%20to%20inform%20him%20that%20we%20had%20lost%20power%20but%20we%20still%20had%20steering.%20I%20did%20it%20just%20to%20avoid%20him%20coming%20too%20close.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20we%20still%20had%20steering%2C%20the%20main%20focus%20was%20figuring%20out%20why%20we%20lost%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20about%20five%20to%2010%20minutes%20for%20power%20to%20be%20restored.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20train%20for%20emergencies%20all%20the%20time%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20general%2C%20life%20at%20sea%20can%20be%20pretty%20calm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMostly%2C%20you%20get%20used%20to%20your%20watch%20being%20pretty%20similar%2C%20unless%20you're%20in%20a%20more%20high-risk%20situation%20like%20coming%20into%20port.%20Because%20emergencies%20don't%20happen%20that%20often%2C%20the%20prudent%20thing%20to%20do%20is%20to%20play%20different%20emergencies%20out%20in%20your%20head%20or%20to%20open%20up%20the%20emergency%20procedures%20binder%20and%20periodically%20read%20through%20it%20just%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20how%20you'd%20handle%20the%20situation%20coincides%20with%20what%20the%20manual%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20weekly%20mandatory%20drills%20on%20everything%20from%20abandoning%20the%20ship%20and%20dealing%20with%20fires%20and%20power%20loss%2C%20to%20responding%20to%20security%20concerns%20like%20bomb%20threats%20or%20piracy.%20We%20regularly%20practice%20various%20emergency%20situations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20ship's%20engineers%20will%20practice%20several%20scenarios%20involving%20power%20loss.%20One%20of%20the%20power%20loss%20drills%20we%20do%20as%20deck%20officers%20is%20practice%20doing%20emergency%20steering%20drills%2C%20and%20that%20involves%20all%20the%20deck%20officers%20and%20the%20captain%20up%20on%20the%20bridge%20going%20through%20the%20procedures%20for%20switching%20the%20steering%20gear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22youtube%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FmC4eE0Hv8xU%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Life-Saving%20Safety%20Equipment%20On%20A%20Cargo%20Ship%20%7C%20Life%20At%20Sea%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20regularly%20reconfirm%20the%20procedures%20and%20how%20to%20do%20them.%20Then%20we%20do%20a%20drill%20where%20we%20practice%20communicating%20with%20an%20engineer%20who%20will%20actually%20go%20from%20the%20engine%20room%20to%20the%20steering%20gear%20room.%20The%20steering%20gear%20room%20is%20usually%20below%20the%20aft%20mooring%20deck%2C%20that's%20where%20the%20big%20electro-hydraulic%20rams%20are%20that%20move%20the%20rudder.%20You%20can%20manually%20control%20that%20entire%20hydraulic%20from%20the%20steering%20room%20using%20different%20control%20levers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20during%20the%20drill%2C%20an%20engineer%20will%20go%20back%20there%20and%20put%20on%20a%20headset%20that's%20connected%20to%20a%20sound-powered%20phone.%20We%20have%20sound-powered%20phones%20on%20board%20as%20a%20backup%20in%20case%20we%20lose%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ships%20use%20sound-powered%20phones%20to%20communicate%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20power%20loss.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660aed833f923f7dab03234e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22733%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EShips%20use%20sound-powered%20phones%20to%20communicate%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20power%20loss.%3Cp%3EPortland%20Press%20Herald%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20the%20engineer%20will%20put%20on%20the%20sound-powered%20phone%20and%20we%20will%20talk%20to%20him%20from%20the%20bridge%20on%20our%20own%20sound-powered%20phone.%20We%20will%20tell%20him%20something%20like%3A%20%26quot%3BPut%20the%20rudder%20starboard%20to%20right%20five%20or%20right%2010%26quot%3B%20and%20he%20will%20manually%20push%20the%20buttons.%20There's%20a%20little%20rudder%20angle%20indicator%20back%20there%20so%20he%20can%20push%20the%20button%20and%20hold%20it%20until%20it%20gets%20to%20the%20rudder%20command%20he%20was%20issued.%20When%20we're%20out%20in%20open%20water%20away%20from%20other%20vessels%2C%20we'll%20practice%20that%20drill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drills%20are%20important%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20enough.%20As%20a%20deck%20officer%2C%20the%20captain%20often%20expects%20you%20to%20prepare%20on%20your%20own%20as%20well.%20One%20way%20we'll%20prepare%20is%20by%20studying%20previous%20accidents%20at%20sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20colleagues%20and%20I%20in%20the%20industry%20have%20talked%20about%20the%20Baltimore%20incident%3A%20what%20could%20have%20gone%20wrong%20or%20what%20we'd%20have%20done%20ourselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaersk%20often%20trains%20us%20based%20on%20previous%20shipping%20incidents%2C%20so%20I'm%20sure%20one%20day%20it%20will%20end%20up%20in%20some%20kind%20of%20training%20at%20the%20academies%20or%20in%20a%20ship%20drill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20it's%20an%20important%20reminder%20for%20those%20of%20us%20who%20work%20at%20sea%20to%20always%20stay%20vigilant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-cargo-ship-workers-prepare-for-emergencies%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712148700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660c63191caec1275a6c1f0b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-cargo-ship-workers-prepare-for-emergencies%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Merchant%20mariner%20Bryan%20Boyle%20breaks%20down%20how%20workers%20are%20trained%20to%20deal%20with%20emergencies%20on%20cargo%20ships.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22gkay%40insider.com%20(Grace%20Kay)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-cargo-ship-workers-prepare-for-emergencies%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Crazy%20Viral%3A%20Bride%20Taapsee%20Pannu's%20Fairytale%20Entry%20At%20Udaipur%20Wedding%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhenna-on-feet-and-ring-in-finger-are-adding-fire-to-taapsee-pannu-s-wedding-rumours-5333734%5C%22%3EDays%2