0for%20over%20millions%20of%20years.%20These%20massive%2C%20rigid%20slabs%20of%20rock%2C%20which%20make%20up%20the%20Earth's%20lithosphere%2C%20are%20in%20constant%20motion%2C%20driven%20by%20the%20forces%20generated%20deep%20within%20the%20planet.%20But%20scientists%20have%20discovered%20a%20colossal%20fissure%20tearing%20through%20the%20southeastern%20part%20of%20Africa%20that%20is%20splitting%20the%20continent%20into%20two%20and%20could%20also%20pave%20way%20for%20the%20Earth's%20sixth%20ocean%20to%20emerge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20planet%20currently%20has%20five%20distinct%20oceans%20-%20Pacific%2C%20Atlantic%2C%20Indian%2C%20Antarctic%20and%20Arctic.%20A%20sixth%20ocean%2C%20if%20formed%2C%20could%20lead%20to%20massive%20changes%20in%20the%20planet's%20geography.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKnown%20as%20the%20East%20African%20Rift%20System%20(EARS)%2C%20it%20was%20first%20discovered%20in%202005%2C%20but%20believed%20to%20have%20initiated%20around%2022%20million%20years%20ago%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.earth.com%2Fnews%2Fafrican-rift-massive-crack-could-split-the-continent-in-half%2F%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3Eearth.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20significant%20surge%20of%20activity%20over%20the%20past%20few%20decades%20has%20spurred%20a%20renewed%20scientific%20interest%20in%20the%20faultline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20East%20African%20Rift%20is%20a%20result%20of%20two%20tectonic%20plates%20-%20the%20Somali%20plate%20in%20the%20east%20and%20Nubian%20plate%20in%20the%20west.%20These%20two%20tectonic%20plates%20have%20been%20drifting%20apart%2C%20causing%20the%20fissure%20to%20deepen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jpost.com%2Fenvironment-and-climate-change%2Farticle-735092%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EJerusalem%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20a%20similar%20phenomenon%20was%20observed%20millions%20of%20years%20ago%20when%20South%20America%20and%20Africa%20were%20divided%20into%20different%20continents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20peer-reviewed%20study%20detailing%20the%20split%20was%20published%20in%20%3Cem%3EEarth%20and%20Planetary%20Science%20Letters%3C%2Fem%3E.%20It%20said%20that%20the%20plates%20separate%20a%20few%20millimetres%20per%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInteresting%20points%20have%20emerged%20from%20the%20deepening%20fissure.%20Experts%20say%20that%20countries%20currently%20landlocked%20in%20Africa%2C%20such%20as%20Ethiopia%20and%20Uganda%2C%20will%20see%20the%20introduction%20of%20a%20coastline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Gulf%20of%20Aden%20and%20the%20Red%20Sea%20will%20flood%20in%20over%20the%20Afar%20region%20and%20into%20the%20East%20African%20Rift%20Valley%20and%20become%20a%20new%20ocean%2C%20and%20that%20part%20of%20East%20Africa%20will%20become%20its%20own%20separate%20small%20continent%2C%26quot%3B%20Ken%20Macdonald%2C%20a%20marine%20geophysicist%20and%20a%20professor%20emeritus%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20told%20Mashable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20researchers%20said%20that%20the%20continent%20will%20not%20completely%20split%20for%20another%205%20to%2010%20million%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712146800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Fne8grc9o_africa-tectonic-plates-1200_625x300_03_April_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fwill-earth-get-a-new-ocean-massive-faultline-in-africa-sparks-speculation-5366960%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20peer-reviewed%20study%20detailing%20the%20split%20was%20published%20in%20Earth%20and%20Planetary%20Science%20Letters.%20It%20said%20that%20the%20plates%20separate%20a%20few%20millimetres%20per%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fwill-earth-get-a-new-ocean-massive-faultline-in-africa-sparks-speculation-5366960%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fwil